                            <comment id="20815" author="jcsahnwaldt" created="Mon, 13 Nov 2006 22:54:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also affects current CVS HEAD.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="20816" author="jcsahnwaldt" created="Mon, 13 Nov 2006 22:55:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;small test case that demonstrates the stack overflow.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="20817" author="jcsahnwaldt" created="Mon, 13 Nov 2006 23:10:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A patch for PropertyPlaceholderConfigurer that should fix the problem. I replaced the single String argument with a Set as recommended by Matej Pivoluska. I didn&apos;t use a LinkedHashSet but just a HashSet to avoid a dependency on JDK 1.4, and the error message is ok without the complete list of visited properties. It currently just includes the first placeholder that &apos;closed the cycle&apos;, which should be enough in most cases to find the problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="20956" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Sat, 18 Nov 2006 02:29:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for pointing this out! Fixed in CVS HEAD, to be released in 2.0.1; will also be backported to 1.2.9.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
